  "ciliary_role": "Interestingly, alteration in HIF expression by hypoxia or pharmacological mimics has also been shown to influence primary cilia length [21241248 , 22084569] and activate the hedgehog pathway [35]. Prolyl hydroxylase inhibition results in ciliary elongation and a more pronounced recruitment of HIF-2α to the ciliary base and sequestration to the ciliary axonome. Elongation drives ciliary sequestration leading to negative regulation of HIF-2α expression and activity.  HIFs have relationship with the primary cilium in inflammation(18774959).",
